.TH "completion_done" 9 "completion_done" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
completion_done \- Test to see if a completion has any waiters
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" completion_done
.BI "(struct completion *x "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "x" 12
completion structure
.SH "RETURN"
0 if there are waiters (\fBwait_for_completion\fP in progress)
1 if there are no waiters.

Note, this will always return true if \fBcomplete_all\fP was called on \fIX\fP.
